1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,080
Let me show you how you can save your Google VADs project as the local mp4 video file.

2
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:18,519
You will need to head to file, add left, then select download as mp4.

3
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:24,080
It will need to process your video so it may take a moment and after that the download

4
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:25,760
will start.

5
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:29,240
And here it is, I already got it on my hard drive.

6
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:31,080
For example video dot mp4.

7
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:36,280
So now I can use that file to play my video locally or to send to somebody.

8
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:44,840
You can also share it, so generate a link to the project in your Google Drive.

9
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:49,400
I hope this short tutorial was helpful, I will see you in the next one.

